{"lemma":"أَلْكَنَيْ","slug":"أَلْكَنَيْ","root":"ل.ك.ن","root_slug":"ل-ك-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ك-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1089"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"inarticulate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lisper"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from لَكِنَ (lakina)."},"ipa":["/ʔal.kan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1089","headword_ar":"اَلِكْنِى","root":"Alk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alaka","text_ar":"اَلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “he sent;” and is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aA^olikoniY","text_ar":"اَاْلِكْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the [second] hemzeh being transposed and placed after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", it becomes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloy^ikoniY","text_ar":"اَلْيِكْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then the hemzeh has its vowel transferred to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is thrown out; as is done in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malakN","text_ar":"مَلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^olakN","text_ar":"مَاْلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maloA^akN","text_ar":"مَلْاَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malakN","text_ar":"مَلَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IB in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lwk","text_ar":"لوك"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Be thou my messenger;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bear thou my message;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is often used by the poets. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lwk","text_ar":"لوك"},{"kind":"text","text":".) Accord. to IAmb, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alikoniY A_ilaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"اَلِكْنِى اـِلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"send thou me to such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but I do not know any instance in which this meaning is applicable:] and the original form is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloy^ikoniY","text_ar":"اَلْيِكْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, if from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aluwku","text_ar":"الاَلُوكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the original form is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aA^olikoniY","text_ar":"اَاْلِكْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": and he also says that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou my messenger to such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alikoniY A_ilayohaA birisaAlapK","text_ar":"اَلِكْنِى اـِلَيْهَا بِرِسَالَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which should properly mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Send thou me to her with a message:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it is an inverted phrase; since the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou my messenger to her with this message"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rather with a message"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alikoniY A_ilayohaA biAls~alaAmi","text_ar":"اَلِكْنِى اـِلَيْهَا بِالسَّلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"convey thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"communicate thou, to her my salutation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou my messenger to her"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with salutation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and sometimes this [prep.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is suppressed, so that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alikoniY A_ilayohaA Als~alaAma","text_ar":"اَلِكْنِى اـِلَيْهَا السَّلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": sometimes, also, the person sent is he to whom the message is sent; as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alikoniY A_ilayoka Als~alaAma","text_ar":"اَلِكْنِى اـِلَيْكَ السَّلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[virtually meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receive thou my salutation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but literally]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou my messenger to thyself with salutation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Lh mentions the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alakotuhu A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اَلَكْتُهُ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with respect to a message, aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uliykuhu","text_ar":"اُلِيكُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaAkahN","text_ar":"اـِلَاكَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; in which case, the hemzeh [in the aor. and inf. n.] is converted into a letter of prolongation. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA^k","text_ar":"لاك"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}